Time: Data from database: World Development Indicators

Country Code: GNI (formerly GNP) is the sum of value added by all resident producers plus any product taxes (less subsidies) not included in the valuation of output plus net receipts of primary income (compensation of employees and property income) from abroad. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
GNI (current US$) [NY.GNP.MKTP.CD]: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.
column6: Economic Policy & Debt: National accounts: US$ at current prices: Aggregate indicators
column9: Because development encompasses many factors - economic, environmental, cultural, educational, and institutional - no single measure gives a complete picture. However, the total earnings of the residents of an economy, measured by its gross national income (GNI), is a good measure of its capacity to provide for the well-being of its people.
